    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-24T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-24T17:00:00-05:00" n="667"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d667">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 654.119/254</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-24T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 24, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4175. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 92. Please note the following and repeat to <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DEL1">Dresel</persName>.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>Your No. 34, Legation 3361, May 14, 5 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d667fn1">Not
                            printed.</note> We agree to your suggestion that raw materials destined
                        for use in Switzerland in the manufacture of munitions for the Allies be not
                        consigned to the S[ociété] S[uisse de] S[urveillance Economique] or reckoned
                        in the Swiss ration. We will rely upon you to insure that such exports are
                            <pb facs="0791" n="1625" xml:id="pg_1625"/> properly safeguarded and
                        will actually be employed in the manufacture of munitions; we understand
                        that you will cable us of what shipments should be licensed in accordance
                        with this special procedure. We feel it important that there should be very
                        close coordination in Switzerland of the representatives of the Associated
                        Governments who are supervising the production of munitions.</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
